GO
CREATE FUNCTION [dbo].[fnBinaryToBase64]
(
    @Var AS VARBINARY(MAX)
)
RETURNS NVARCHAR(MAX)
AS
BEGIN
    RETURN (
        SELECT  @Var AS '*' FOR XML PATH('')
    );
END

/****** Object:  View [dbo].[JobView]    Script Date: 2023/12/13 16:20:17 ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO

CREATE   VIEW [dbo].[JobView]
AS
SELECT                      dbo.tbl_job.JobID, dbo.tbl_job.CompanyID, dbo.tbl_company.CompanyName, dbo.tbl_job.JobRoleID, dbo.tbl_jobrole.JobRoleName, 
                                      dbo.tbl_job.JobTypeID, dbo.tbl_jobtype.JobTypeName, dbo.tbl_job.CategoryID, dbo.tbl_category.CategoryName, dbo.tbl_job.JobLocationID, 
                                      dbo.tbl_joblocation.JobStreetAddress, dbo.tbl_city.CityName, dbo.tbl_country.CountryName, dbo.tbl_job.JobPositionID, dbo.tbl_jobposition.JobPositionName, 
                                      dbo.tbl_job.Allowence, dbo.tbl_job.Salary, dbo.tbl_job.JobDescription, dbo.tbl_job.JobResponsibility, dbo.tbl_job.CreatedDate, dbo.tbl_job.UpdatedDate, 
                                      dbo.tbl_job.Status, [dbo].[fnBinaryToBase64](dbo.tbl_company.CompanyImage) as CompanyImage
FROM                         dbo.tbl_job INNER JOIN
                                      dbo.tbl_company ON dbo.tbl_job.CompanyID = dbo.tbl_company.CompanyID INNER JOIN
                                      dbo.tbl_jobrole ON dbo.tbl_job.JobRoleID = dbo.tbl_jobrole.JobRoleID INNER JOIN
                                      dbo.tbl_jobtype ON dbo.tbl_job.JobTypeID = dbo.tbl_jobtype.JobTypeID INNER JOIN
                                      dbo.tbl_category ON dbo.tbl_job.CategoryID = dbo.tbl_category.CategoryID INNER JOIN
                                      dbo.tbl_joblocation ON dbo.tbl_job.JobLocationID = dbo.tbl_joblocation.JobLocationID INNER JOIN
                                      dbo.tbl_jobposition ON dbo.tbl_job.JobPositionID = dbo.tbl_jobposition.JobPositionID INNER JOIN
                                      dbo.tbl_city ON dbo.tbl_joblocation.CityID = dbo.tbl_city.CityID INNER JOIN
                                      dbo.tbl_country ON dbo.tbl_city.CountryID = dbo.tbl_country.CountryID

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[sp_searchjob]
(
	@companyname varchar(100),
	@jrolename varchar(20),
    @countryname varchar(100)
) 
AS
Begin
if not exists (SELECT * FROM JobView WHERE CompanyName = @companyname OR JobTypeName = @jrolename OR CountryName = @countryname)
    Begin
            SELECT * FROM JobView
    End
Else
	if exists (SELECT * FROM JobView WHERE CompanyName = @companyname OR JobTypeName = @jrolename OR CountryName = @countryname)
		Begin
			SELECT * FROM JobView WHERE CompanyName = @companyname OR JobTypeName = @jrolename OR CountryName = @countryname
		End  
	else
		Begin
			SELECT * FROM JobView WHERE JobTypeName = @jrolename AND CountryName = @countryname OR CompanyName = @companyname
		End 
End
GO
